Definition

Embeddings are numerical vector representations of words, sentences, or documents that capture their meaning and relationships. Similar meanings have vectors that are close together in vector space.

Real-world Analogy

Imagine plotting cities on a map. Cities that are geographically close are easier to travel between. Similarly, words with similar meanings have embeddings that are close together.

Salesforce Example

A Salesforce AI Assistant can understand that "Lead", "Prospect", and "Potential Customer" are semantically related because their embeddings are similar.

Interview Question

Q: Why do AI systems convert text into embeddings instead of processing plain text directly?